    <stitle>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - MXT - COMPONENT AND RADIATOR REMOVal - RADIATOR SHROUD AND FRAME</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>RADIATOR SHROUD AND FRAME</title>
        <para>After locating and securing the radiator assembly in a safely supported position on the floor or work
            bench area, remove frame and fan shroud (Figures 23 through 26).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200820" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1200820.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="264px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 23. Example Radiator Frame Disassemble</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR CORE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. RADIATOR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. RADIATOR FRAME</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove upper frame bolts.</para>
            <figure id="f1200821" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1200821.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Example Radiator Upper Frame Removal (View Lying Flat)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. UPPER RADIATOR FRAME BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate, loosen and remove the charge air cooler mounting bolts from under the surface of the
                radiator cross frame (Figure 25).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the remainder of radiator frame bolts on each side of radiator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the bolts for the fan shroud assembly (Figure 26).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200822" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1200822.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="224px"/>
            <caption>Figure 25. Example Radiator Frame Removal (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>3. RADIATOR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1201926" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201926.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="408px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 26. Example Radiator Fan Shroud Removal</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
